       Change Summary Explanation
       The FY 2026 total increase of $82.687 million is due to an increase of $96.476 million to fund Hypersonics, a decrease of $13.080 million to T&E range
       modernization and Autonomy in order to fund part of zero basing reprogram for Developmental Test Aircraft Capacity, inflation, and other adjustments to
       programs, and $0.709 million decrease in Cyberspace and Avionics Cyber due to reduced costs of requirements and other adjustments.

       The FY 2026 request was reduced by $0.672 million for Advisory and Assistance Services to promote efficiencies and advance the policies of the Administration
       in alignment with Executive Order 14222, "Implementing the President's Department of Government Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiative.”

